1. Merge Sort
Merge Sort is a sorting algorithm used to arrange numbers in order.
The main idea is divide and conquer.
First, the list is divided into smaller parts until each part contains only one element. Then these small parts are merged back together in sorted order.

2.Sliding Window

Sliding Window is a technique used to process a part of an array or string at a time.
Instead of checking every possible group of elements again and again, we keep a window of fixed size and move it step by step.

3. Two Pointer Technique

The Two Pointer technique uses two positions in an array to solve problems efficiently.
Usually:
One pointer starts from the beginning
One pointer starts from the end

4. Stack

A Stack is a data structure that follows the rule:
LIFO (Last In, First Out)
The last element added to the stack is the first one removed.

5. Binary Tree

A Binary Tree is a hierarchical data structure where each node can have at most two children.

6. Duplicate Detection
Duplicate detection means checking whether a list contains repeated values.

7. Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)

The Longest Increasing Subsequence problem finds the longest sequence of numbers that increases continuously.

8. Anagram

Two words are called anagrams if they contain the same letters but in a different order.